    • Select all fields from populations with records of 2015 that are larger than 1.15 times the average life expectancy
    SELECT *
  FROM populations
WHERE year = '2015'
  AND life_expectancy > 
  (SELECT AVG(life_expectancy * 1.15)
   FROM populations
   WHERE year = 2015);

    Subquery (inside SELECT)

    • Ïù¥ Í≤ΩÏö∞, ASÎ°ú alias Ìï¥Ïïº Ìï®!
    • GET the country and number of cities per country
    • Order the result in descending order of the number and limit the result to 9 countries
    SELECT countries.name AS country, COUNT(*) AS cities_num
  FROM cities
    INNER JOIN countries
    ON countries.code = cities.country_code
GROUP BY country
ORDER BY cities_num DESC, country
LIMIT 9;


# ÏúÑ ÏΩîÎìúÏôÄ Í∞ôÏùÄ ÏΩîÎìú
SELECT countries.name AS country,
  (SELECT COUNT(*)
   FROM cities
   WHERE countries.code = cities.country_code) AS cities_num
FROM countries
ORDER BY cities_num DESC, country
LIMIT 9;

    Subquery (inside FROM)

    • Ïù¥ Í≤ΩÏö∞, ASÎ°ú alias Ìï¥Ïïº Ìï®!
    • Get the number of languages spoken for each country, identified by the country‚Äôs local name
    SELECT local_name, subquery.lang_num
  FROM countries,
  	(SELECT code, COUNT(*) AS lang_num
  	 FROM languages
  	 GROUP BY code) AS subquery
  WHERE countries.code = subquery.code
ORDER BY lang_num DESC;
